Description. Body (
Fig. 4
) reddish-brown; head, elytra and anterior part of tergites often darker, reddish-brown to brownish; legs, palpi and antenna brownish-yellow.

Distribution. Northwestern Yunnan (
Fig. 8
). The species is widely distributed along the northern and central parts of the Gaoligong Shan range. One specimen was collected at the opposite side of the Salween river in the Nu Shan range.
